# Code Style

## Formatting

- Prettier is the single source of truth for formatting
- Config is in `.prettierrc` at project root
- Run `npm run format` to auto-fix, `npm run format:check` in CI

## Linting

- ESLint handles both code quality and formatting (via eslint-plugin-prettier)
- `npm run lint` auto-fixes, `npm run lint:check` for CI (no auto-fix)
- Bug-catching rules are enabled: no-self-compare, eqeqeq, no-eval, etc.

## Pre-commit Hooks

- Husky runs lint-staged on every commit
- Staged `.ts` files are auto-linted and formatted
- Commits will be blocked if ESLint errors are found

## NestJS Conventions

- Controllers handle HTTP concerns only (validation, response shaping)
- Services contain business logic
- Repositories handle database access
- Use dependency injection, not direct imports of services
- DTOs use class-validator decorators for input validation
